The paper focuses on detecting face tampering in videos using deep learning techniques, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) categories. The paper also discusses the limitations of traditional image forensics techniques, which suggests that it may belong to the computer security and cryptography (cs.CR) category. The use of deep learning networks also indicates that it may belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories.
